1 "7-14-241. Procedure to be included in district or to remove an addition to or existing property
2 from a district. (1) A real property owner may petition to have that owner's property included in a district. The
3 addition of the real property owner's property must be approved by a majority vote of the transportation board.
4 (2) An area added to a district pursuant to this part may be removed from the district if the area
5 does not directly receive receive direct transportation services from the district and 51% of the qualified voters
6 in the area to be removed sign a petition requesting to be removed from the district. The removal of the area is
7 effective 60 days after submission of the petition to the transportation board unless within that time, it is
8 determined that the petition contains insufficient signatures for removal of the area. An insufficient petition must
9 be returned to the petitioners, who may resubmit a corrected version within 90 days. A transportation district
10 shall maintain an inventory or map that clearly delineates areas added to the district.
11 (3) A real property owner or owners that are part of the existing district may be removed from the
12 district if the area has not received direct transportation services from the district in the last 5 years and 51% of
13 the qualified voters in the area to be removed sign a petition requesting to be removed from the district. The
14 removal of the area is effective 60 days after submission of the petition to the transportation board unless within
15 that time, it is determined that the petition contains insufficient signatures for removal of the area. An insufficient
16 petition must be returned to the petitioners, who may resubmit a corrected version within 90 days.
17 (3)(4) (a) All Except as provided in subsection (4)(b), all property within any addition to a district is
18 subject to all existing indebtedness of the district.
19 (b) (i) Property within an area removed from a district is not subject to the district's existing
20 indebtedness if the area was added to the district within 5 years of the date on which the petition for removal
21 was submitted to the transportation board.
22 (ii) Property within an area removed from a district is not subject to the district's existing
23 indebtedness if the area has not received direct transportation services within 5 years of the date on which the
24 petition for removal was submitted to the transportation board."
